<div class="js-curloc-error-modal curloc-error-modal hidden">
<div class="modal_head">
<h2>Oops, we can't find your location</h2>
</div>
<div class="modal_body">
<div class="curloc-permission-denied hidden">
<p>
First, try refreshing the page and clicking Current Location again. Make sure you click <b>Allow</b> or <b>Grant Permissions</b> if your browser asks for your location. If your browser doesn't ask you, try these steps:
</p>
<div class="chrome hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>At the top of your Chrome window, near the web address, click <b>the green lock labeled Secure</b>.</li>
<li>In the window that pops up, make sure <b>Location</b> is set to <b>Ask</b> or <b>Allow</b>.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Reload this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
If you're still having trouble, check out <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/142065?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&hl=en&oco=0" target="_blank">Google's support page</a>.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="opera hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>At the top of your Opera window, near the web address, you should see a <b>gray location pin</b>. Click it.</li>
<li>In the window that pops up, click <b>Clear This Setting</b></li>
<li>You're good to go! Reload this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
If you're still having trouble, check out <a target="_blank">Opera's support page</a>.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="safari hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>Click <b>Safari</b> in the Menu Bar at the top of the screen, then <b>Preferences</b>.</li>
<li>Click the <b>Privacy</b> tab.</li>
<li>Under <b>Website use of location services</b>, click <b>Prompt for each website once each day</b> or <b>Prompt for each website one time only</b>.</li>
<li>MacOS may now prompt you to enable Location Services. If it does, follow its instructions to enable Location Services for Safari.</li>
<li>Close the Privacy menu and refresh the page. Try using Current Location search again. If it works, great! If not, read on for more instructions.</li>
<li>Back in the <b>Privacy</b> dialog, Click <b>Manage Website Data...</b> and type <b>yelp.com</b> into the search bar.</li>
<li>Click the <b>yelp.com</b> entry and click Remove.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Close the Settings tab, reload this Yelp page, and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
If you're still having trouble, check out <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT204690" target="_blank">Safari's support page</a>.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="firefox hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>At the top of your Firefox window, to the left of the web address, you should see a <b>green lock</b>. Click it.</li>
<li>In the window that pops up, you should see <b>Blocked</b> or <b>Blocked Temporarily</b> next to <b>Access Your Location</b>. Click the <b>x</b> next to this line.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Refresh this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
If you're still having trouble, check out <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/geolocation/" target="_blank">Firefox's support page</a>.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="ie hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>Click the <b>gear</b> in the upper-right hand corner of the window, then <b>Internet options</b>.</li>
<li>Click the <b>Privacy</b> tab in the new window that just appeared.</li>
<li>Uncheck the box labeled <b>Never allow websites to request your physical location</b> if it's already checked.</li>
<li>Click the button labeled <b>Clear Sites</b>.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Click <b>OK</b>, then refresh this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="edge hidden">
<ol class="modal_section u-bg-color">
<li>At the top-right hand corner of the window, click the <b>button with three dots on it</b>, then <b>Settings</b>.</li>
<li>Click <b>Choose what to clear</b> underneath <b>Clear browsing data</b>.</li>
<li>Click <b>Show more</b>, then make sure only the box labeled <b>Location permissions</b> is checked.</li>
<li>Click <b>Clear</b>.</li>
<li>You're good to go! Refresh this Yelp page and try your search again.</li>
</ol>
<p>
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
<div class="default hidden">
<p>
Oops! We don't recognize the web browser you're currently using. Try checking the browser's help menu, or searching the Web for instructions to turn on HTML5 Geolocation for your browser.
You can also search near a city, place, or address instead.
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="curloc-unavailable hidden">
Something broke and we're not sure what. Try again later, or search near a city, place, or address instead.
</div>
<div class="curloc-timeout hidden">
We couldn't find you quickly enough! Try again later, or search near a city, place, or address instead.
</div>
<div class="curloc-inaccurate hidden">
We couldn't find an accurate position. If you're using a laptop or tablet, try moving it somewhere else and give it another go. Or, search near a city, place, or address instead.
</div>
</div>

<div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
<meta itemprop="author" content="Katherine C.">
<div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
<meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="2.0">
</div>
<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2017-12-21">
<p itemprop="description">This is a lively spot on a pretty busy street. I came here for brunch on a Saturday morning around 11am. By then, it would&#39;ve been at least a 1.5hr wait. However, my friend brought her dog so we sat outside, not the patio but the seats in front of the restaurant. The tables outside in the front are first come, first served. The staff is friendly, however I felt the service was slow. I felt that we were often forgotten since we were sitting outside. It took forever before someone came to take our order and I had to ask several times for one coffee refill.

Personally, I hate going out for brunch. I think brunch is overpriced. Who would pay $15 for avocado toast, when you can make that yourself for a few dollars? But I suppose going out for brunch is more for the social aspect. Anyways, let&#39;s get back on topic...

The food is on the pricier side, but I think it&#39;s because they have a no tipping rule. The food itself was ok. I liked how they put entire garlic cloves in their potatoes. They leave the skin on so they&#39;re really crispy. My husband ate them with the skin on, but I prefer peeling them off. Other than that, I&#39;ve had better. The brunch menu didn&#39;t appeal to me much, but the options for dinner looked really good. I think I would try going back for dinner instead.<p>
</div>

<div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
<meta itemprop="author" content="Oliver L.">
<div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
<meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="3.0">
</div>
<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2017-12-11">
<p itemprop="description">I came here for brunch one weekend at the behest of my friends. I opted for the smoked salmon Eggs Benedict, which was decent - the eggs were cooked nicely and I liked the home fries, which featured roasted garlic cloves that made for a flavorful side. We also shared a pumpkin pancake dish that was mediocre; while the pancakes were fluffy, we all agreed that it was overly sweet. Our server was friendly enough, and the interior is well-lit with interesting decor.

This place seems to get a lot of hype for brunch and I must admit I don&#39;t quite understand why - while I enjoyed my meal, there wasn&#39;t anything exceptional about it that warranted the wait.<p>
</div>

<p itemprop="description">Still my favorite brunch place. It&#39;s a convenient location in Cole Valley, right off the N Judah. Nowadays, I usually make my own french toast and eggs but sometimes you need a day with your friends and gather at a good brunch place. The wait is a bit long but it is proof of the yumminess. French toast, ricotta pancakes, eggs Benedict are just some of the items we order. Bring a sweater or jacket just in case you get assigned outdoor seating. There are heat lamps but SF weather can be rather cool.
It&#39;s also a delight to go on Tuesdays for free corkage nights. We went a while back and had a nice dinner. I also like the idea that it is no tip Bc they build prices to account for employee benefits.<p>

<p itemprop="description">Thank you, Zazie, for setting the bar for brunch food. They serve some of the most mouthwatering brunch dishes I&#39;ve had yet. My boyfriend and I decided to start off our SF date here, ordering:
- Monaco poached eggs (prosciutto and tomatoes)
- St. Trop poached eggs (smoked salmon, capers, red onions) - bursting with flavor!
- French Toast Tahiti - moist and fluffy french toast with warm caramelized bananas = YES. I&#39;m not that big a fan of intensely sweet foods but wow, this blew my mind. It&#39;s something you&#39;ve got to try to understand.

Service was unfortunately lacking so I subtracted a star from my review. They were understaffed that day and we found ourselves waiting a bunch to get our waiter&#39;s attention both to order food in the beginning and to get the check at the end. Hopefully they&#39;ll be better staffed next time!<p>

<div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
<meta itemprop="author" content="Justine D.">
<div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
<meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="4.0">
</div>
<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2017-06-09">
<p itemprop="description">Main reason I came to Zazie is I was looking for a place that offered Brunch options during the week. Upon reading the menu online I saw that Zazie is tip free as their &#34;menu prices include a living wage, revenue share, paid family leave, fully funded health &amp; dental insurance, paid time off, and a 401(k) with employer match for all of our hard working employees.&#34; To me that is huge, especially in this day and age.

It was packed on a rainy Thursday at noon, but my group of 3 only waited about 30 mins. We had a very comfortable seat and did not feel crammed in like sardines. Table, however, was small for the amount of food we ordered. I like that you can order 1, 2, or 3 benedicts, pancakes, french toast, etc. I highly recommend the miracle pancakes. I got to get my fat girl on with bread pudding pancakes, which were life changing. The divorce benedict was good, but I&#39;ve honestly had better. And my husband really enjoyed his Croque Monsieur, which was huge. Our waitress was also lovely. We definitely were those a-holes that sat for awhile after our meal chatting and none of the employees made us feel that we had to get up and leave. Would definitely come back here next time I&#39;m in the Bay.

I&#39;m pretty sure they have a private room in the back that can accommodate a group (we saw a wedding reception of approximately 20 people). Not to sure on those details though.<p>
</div>

I would expect 30-60 minutes wait. But there are seats ( 4 small tables ) outside which has no wait time, if is first come first serve. <a href="javascript:;" class="js-read-less">Read less</a>
</p>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-2 rating-large" title="2.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="2.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
12/21/2017
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">This is a lively spot on a pretty busy street. I came here for brunch on a Saturday morning around 11am. By then, it would&#39;ve been at least a 1.5hr wait. However, my friend brought her dog so we sat outside, not the patio but the seats in front of the restaurant. The tables outside in the front are first come, first served. The staff is friendly, however I felt the service was slow. I felt that we were often forgotten since we were sitting outside. It took forever before someone came to take our order and I had to ask several times for one coffee refill. <br><br>Personally, I hate going out for brunch. I think brunch is overpriced. Who would pay $15 for avocado toast, when you can make that yourself for a few dollars? But I suppose going out for brunch is more for the social aspect. Anyways, let&#39;s get back on topic...<br><br>The food is on the pricier side, but I think it&#39;s because they have a no tipping rule. The food itself was ok. I liked how they put entire garlic cloves in their potatoes. They leave the skin on so they&#39;re really crispy. My husband ate them with the skin on, but I prefer peeling them off. Other than that, I&#39;ve had better. The brunch menu didn&#39;t appeal to me much, but the options for dinner looked really good. I think I would try going back for dinner instead.</p>
</div>

<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-3 rating-large" title="3.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="3.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
12/11/2017
</span>

</div>

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">
<svg role="img" class="icon_svg">
<use xlink:href="#18x18_check_in" />
</svg>
</span>1 check-in
</span>
</li>

</ul>


<p lang="en">I came here for brunch one weekend at the behest of my friends. I opted for the smoked salmon Eggs Benedict, which was decent - the eggs were cooked nicely and I liked the home fries, which featured roasted garlic cloves that made for a flavorful side. We also shared a pumpkin pancake dish that was mediocre; while the pancakes were fluffy, we all agreed that it was overly sweet. Our server was friendly enough, and the interior is well-lit with interesting decor.<br><br>This place seems to get a lot of hype for brunch and I must admit I don&#39;t quite understand why - while I enjoyed my meal, there wasn&#39;t anything exceptional about it that warranted the wait.</p>
</div>

<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-5 rating-large" title="5.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="5.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
8/18/2018
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Still my favorite brunch place. It&#39;s a convenient location in Cole Valley, right off the N Judah. Nowadays, I usually make my own french toast and eggs but sometimes you need a day with your friends and gather at a good brunch place. The wait is a bit long but it is proof of the yumminess. French toast, ricotta pancakes, eggs Benedict are just some of the items we order. Bring a sweater or jacket just in case you get assigned outdoor seating. There are heat lamps but SF weather can be rather cool. <br>It&#39;s also a delight to go on Tuesdays for free corkage nights. We went a while back and had a nice dinner. I also like the idea that it is no tip Bc they build prices to account for employee benefits.</p>
</div>

<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-5 rating-large" title="5.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="5.0 star rating">

<span class="rating-qualifier">
11/21/2017
<small class="bullet-before has-archived-review">
<span aria-hidden="true" style="width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-update icon--size-18 icon--warning">

<span >

<p lang="en">I was wrong, I was so wrong. Zazie has officially topped Mymy in my book for the best brunch in the city. I switched to the pancakes this time from the benedicts and the pumpkin miracle pancakes rocked my world. They were quite possibly the best I&#39;ve ever had. Those pancakes combined with the cozy interiors and living wages for their employees, I&#39;m sold. I&#39;ll definitely be a new regular here soon!</p>

<span class="rating-qualifier">
1/26/2014
<strong class="bullet-before has-previous-review">

<span class="js-expandable-comment comment-truncated">
<span class="js-content-toggleable">Quick tip - tables outside the restaurant are first come first serve, and very few people seem to…</span>
<span class="js-content-toggleable hidden">Quick tip - tables outside the restaurant are first come first serve, and very few people seem to know this (even though there are signs outside). try to snag one if you can!<br><br>Came here on a Saturday morning around 10am. Wait was ~45 minutes, but went down the street to get some coffee, killed most of the wait. <br><br>I ordered:<br>(+) french toast tahiti.<br>Pretty good. Walnut banana filling inside is a little heavy, french toast itself a bit dry without the filling (although you can always douse it with the syrup that comes with the meal). I was surprised that I did not like this item more as it is so raved about on yelp. A little underwhelmed but definitely still good.<br><br>Others ordered:<br>-Poached eggs la mer.<br>with fresh hand picked dungeness crab, green onions, and haas avocados<br>-Poached eggs monaco.<br>with Zoe&#39;s proscuitto and tomatoes provencales<br>great because proscuitto is my new favorite thing.<br><br>Both were well received by the friends.<br><br>Pros:<br>(+) portion control.<br>option to order 1, 2, or 3 eggs/ pieces, etc. as you desire with staggered prices.  very good for groups.<br>(+) service.<br>very attentive waiters, friendly and knowledgable.<br>(+) garden patio.<br>very cute garden patio with heat lamps and string lights. very SF, great ambiance.<br><br>Cons (very minor):<br>(-) smallest bathroom ever.<br>seriously small.<br>(-) tiniest water cups ever.<br>seriously not thirst quenching.</span>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-4 rating-large" title="4.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="4.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
6/6/2016
</span>

</div>

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">
<svg role="img" class="icon_svg">
<use xlink:href="#18x18_check_in" />
</svg>
</span>1 check-in
</span>
</li>

</ul>


<p lang="en">Thank you, Zazie, for setting the bar for brunch food. They serve some of the most mouthwatering brunch dishes I&#39;ve had yet. My boyfriend and I decided to start off our SF date here, ordering:<br>- Monaco poached eggs (prosciutto and tomatoes) <br>- St. Trop poached eggs (smoked salmon, capers, red onions) - bursting with flavor!<br>- French Toast Tahiti - moist and fluffy french toast with warm caramelized bananas = YES. I&#39;m not that big a fan of intensely sweet foods but wow, this blew my mind. It&#39;s something you&#39;ve got to try to understand.<br><br>Service was unfortunately lacking so I subtracted a star from my review. They were understaffed that day and we found ourselves waiting a bunch to get our waiter&#39;s attention both to order food in the beginning and to get the check at the end. Hopefully they&#39;ll be better staffed next time!</p>

<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-4 rating-large" title="4.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="4.0 star rating">

<span class="rating-qualifier">
3/22/2018

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">

<p lang="en">Very cute space, fast service, and good value. The egg benedicts are worth trying. The hollandaise sauce was very tasty and the home fries were perfect. Not quite 5 stars as the dish wasn&#39;t fully warm, and the cheese and avocado portions were very small.</p>

<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-5 rating-large" title="5.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="5.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
9/22/2018
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Went to the restaurant with a friend. Decided to order the chicken liver pate app to share; friend ordered Le Canard for entree; I ordered the seafood stew; and we finished with the goat cheesecake and baked hot chocolate for dessert. Both of us thought the food was great (personally I found the hot chocolate to be a bit too sweet, but friend found it irresistible so no doubt it&#39;s perfect as a guilty pleasure.<br><br>Tips are already factored in the menu price, like how it is in France. Found the service to be excellent and much better than traditional American restaurant. Overall had a wonderful time and would recommend to all.</p>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-5 rating-large" title="5.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="5.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
5/29/2018
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">You got me Zazie...I have left my heart in San Francisco!  Mainly because I&#39;ll not likely return for quite some time but if I could you&#39;d be my first stop for breakfast!!!  The cappuccino was a delicious start. It always good to see a breakfast place with great coffee!  Then the ambiance was what hit us. Such a cool vibe outside in back. Even sitting so close to folks wasn&#39;t a bother.  The ethos was so enjoyable that we didn&#39;t mind waiting for our food.  When it did arrive though...be still my heart!  The Benedict was over the top!  Fresh avocado, bacon, and the creamiest hollandaise on PERFECTLY, and I do mean perfectly, cooked poached eggs. The. The banana/walnut French toast???  Why did we order so much food???  But it too was delicious.  The banana purée in between with the walnuts mixed in was a perfect filling.  We nearly didn&#39;t even need to use the syrup!  But...not wanting to be rude...we did anyway!!!  Even the syrup was off the chain!  Give me my heart back Zazie!!!</p>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-3 rating-large" title="3.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="3.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
4/19/2016
</span>

</div>

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">
<svg role="img" class="icon_svg">
<use xlink:href="#18x18_check_in" />
</svg>
</span>2 check-ins
</span>
</li>

</ul>


<p lang="en">My quest to find unique french toast and pancakes. <br><br>- French Toast Tahiti. CHECK!<br>- Gingerbread Pancakes. CHECK!<br>- Challah French Toast. CHECK!<br><br>My feeling towards those sweet serving was somewhat underwhelmed. The first time I had Zazie was decent. This time I had it again and was not impressed with their popular items. Even the savory omelette wasn&#39;t pleasing. <br><br>I think I prefer Kitchen Story mascarpone stuffed deep-fried French toast or Betty&#39;s Diner soufflé pancakes much better. <br><br>The service was still friendly and helpful. Overall, a decent breakfast joint if you don&#39;t mind the wait.</p>

<div class="review-wrapper">
<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-4 rating-large" title="4.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="4.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
6/9/2017
</span>

</div>

<p lang="en">Main reason I came to Zazie is I was looking for a place that offered Brunch options during the week.  Upon reading the menu online I saw that Zazie is tip free as their &#34;menu prices include a living wage, revenue share, paid family leave, fully funded health &amp; dental insurance, paid time off, and a 401(k) with employer match for all of our hard working employees.&#34;  To me that is huge, especially in this day and age.<br><br>It was packed on a rainy Thursday at noon, but my group of 3 only waited about 30 mins.  We had a very comfortable seat and did not feel crammed in like sardines.  Table, however, was small for the amount of food we ordered.  I like that you can order 1, 2, or 3 benedicts, pancakes, french toast, etc.  I highly recommend the miracle pancakes.  I got to get my fat girl on with bread pudding pancakes, which were life changing.  The divorce benedict was good, but I&#39;ve honestly had better.  And my husband really enjoyed his Croque Monsieur, which was huge.  Our waitress was also lovely.  We definitely were those a-holes that sat for awhile after our meal chatting and none of the employees made us feel that we had to get up and leave.  Would definitely come back here next time I&#39;m in the Bay.<br><br>I&#39;m pretty sure they have a private room in the back that can accommodate a group (we saw a wedding reception of approximately 20 people).  Not to sure on those details though.</p>

<div class="review-content">
<div class="biz-rating biz-rating-large clearfix">
<div >



<div class="i-stars i-stars--regular-3 rating-large" title="3.0 star rating">
<img class="offscreen" height="303" src="https://s3-media2.fl.yelpcdn.com/assets/srv0/yelp_design_web/9b34e39ccbeb/assets/img/stars/stars.png" width="84" alt="3.0 star rating">
</div>



</div>
<span class="rating-qualifier">
5/3/2016
</span>

</div>

<ul class="review-tags">
<li class="review-tags_item">

<span >
<span aria-hidden="true" style="fill: #0077bc; width: 18px; height: 18px;" class="icon icon--18-check-in icon--size-18 u-space-r-half">
<svg role="img" class="icon_svg">
<use xlink:href="#18x18_check_in" />
</svg>
</span>1 check-in
</span>
</li>

</ul>


<p lang="en">We came here on a Tuesday and there was no wait so we decided to give it a try.  Even though everything was pretty decent, I have mixed feelings about this place.<br><br>I asked the waiter what he&#39;d recommend and he didn&#39;t really have much to say, so I asked how&#39;s the un, deux, trois? He said good, so I went with it.  I didn&#39;t realize there was different types of un, deux, trois nor he explained he just got me the buttermilk pancakes, bacon and poached eggs (he did ask how I wanted my eggs cooked). It seems that the miracle pancakes are the things to get, if only I&#39;d have known (grrrr). My fiance got a special of the day which had eggs and a mushroom base sauce. She loved her dish, as for me it was alright.  The pancake was good, however, when I saw miracle pancakes sly by me to the table next to me my brain went on overload. The un,deux,trois was nothing to brag about, if I could go back  I&#39;d get a pancake stack.<br><br>Even though prices were a bit high, tip is included in those prices.  I will come back for the miracle pancakes.</p>

<p lang="en">This place is super cute and I loved all we had. I split the French toast and Eggs Benedict with my sister, absolutely delicious! The waitress was really nice and the tips were already included in the prices. I highly recommend this place.</p>

<p lang="en">Great brunch place! It&#39;s quite busy, but so far haven&#39;t had to wait long. Love coming here with my close friends, even after one of us moved away. Great environment for catching up. Customer service is amazing and overall, clean place. Tried a couple things on their menu already and everything was yummy!</p>

<div class="ywidget js-from-biz-owner">
<h3>From the business</h3>
<p>
Zazie has been rated &#34;Best Brunch in the Bay Area&#34; by multiple publications over the last 18 years, including the SF Chronicle, Bay Guardian, and SF Weekly. Michael Bauer last …

</p>

<a class="link-more" href="javascript:;">
Learn more about Zazie
<span class="offscreen">, Opens a popup</span>
</a>

<div class="hidden from-biz-owner-wrapper">
<div class="from-biz-owner-content">
<h3>Specialties</h3>
<p>
Zazie has been rated &#34;Best Brunch in the Bay Area&#34; by multiple publications over the last 18 years, including the SF Chronicle, Bay Guardian, and SF Weekly. &nbsp;Michael Bauer last reviewed Zazie with the headline, &#34;Zazie brings brunch to new heights.&#34; &nbsp;We are famous for our specialty pancakes, including Gingerbread Pancakes with lemon curd and roasted bosc pears, Lemon-Ricotta pancakes, and Sugar Pie Pumpkin Spice Pancakes. &nbsp;Our benedict dishes are also exceptional, with the best hollandaise in town.<br><br>For dinner, we specialize in &nbsp;Southern French/ Californian cuisine, with slow braised dishes and fresh fish. &nbsp;Our wine list concentrates on small, family owned winemakers with less than 500 case productions. &nbsp;The menu changes seasonally; check online for updates.<br><br>Our heated garden patio is one of the few places in SF where you can comfortably dine outside under the stars, and inside the soaring ceilings and original 1876 brick wall make Zazie a unique SF treat.
</p>

<h3>History</h3>
<p>
Established in 1992.
</p>

<p>
Catherine Opoix opened Zazie as one of the first restaurants in what was to become the bustling restaurant scene of sleepy Cole Valley in 1992. &nbsp;Jennifer Piallat became general manager in 2000, then purchased the restaurant in 2005, bringing long time server Mario Rojas up to general manager. &nbsp;Since becoming the first non-union restaurant in SF to offer full benefits and a retirement plan, Zazie now retains an amazing staff who are knowledgable and eager to please.
</p>

</div>

</div>
